inn1.comm: tidy start, landing it on the dime and How goes back to defend
first runs, tucked off the hips into the gap backward of square leg as Anderon drops short, Broad has to run around and field and returns a good throw
good line again, bringing How forward to defend to point
dragged in too short and How mistimes his attempt at a pull, instead chopping into the ground and midwicket moves in to field
hint of movement, Anderson pitching back of a length, How defends
tucked up and he works the ball off the hips to midwicket
hits a length and McCullum's already walked across his stumps to try and nudge if fine but he can't get bat on it and the ball drops near his feet, Broad runs in
fuller length, with plenty of away movement, and he leaves it be
works it wider this time, moving it off the seam and trying to get McCullum chasing but he covers the stumps and leaves it be, good carry to Ambrose
off-stump line now and McCullum watchfully defends it
gets bat on this one, tapping towards Pietersen at extra cover and sprinting off, he collects and has a back-hand flip at the stumps but misses, so McCullum's off the mark
hits a length and comes in to How, who gets back and tries to tuck it fine but ends up getting a leading-edge of sorts which falls well in front of cover
gets right outside his crease and taps a short and wide one straight to Collingwood at backward point, that ball was there to be slapped away
there we go, thats gone to the fence, McCullum getting up tall and punching this one off the back foot past the men in the covers
oh he's slapped the pants off that one, has McCullum, just swivelling off the front foot and pulling one from back of a length rows back into deep midwicket where a fan drops the catch, stunning shot
expensive over so far, as Anderson overcompensates by bowling full on the toes and thats clipped past a diving deep square leg fielder, racing across the grass
again, too straight and thats tucked away, Wright chases it down
and then, just like that, Anderson bowls it fullish outside off stump and McCullum thumps it ferociously but finds a leaping Pietersen at mid-off
short of a length and punched off the back foot to the man at cover
fuller now, well outside off, and How leaves it be for Ambrose
too short on the stumps and thats pullled away with disdain, and power
fullish and widish again and How goes back to leaving
slips down leg and How is late on the shot, Broad half appeals
hmm, thats a bit wide again and How thinks about slashing it away but holds back, umpire Steve Davis doesn't say anything so thats the over
on the pads and again easily turned out to deep midwicket for one
gets back and defends a shortish one, gets an inside-edge back onto his boot, follows the ball to point, Taylor initiates the manic single and Collingwood is late to swoop in on the ball
slower ball, fuller and straightens and beats his forward prod
full and swinging in and he on-drives to mid-on for a quick single
back of a good length and How patiently defends to cover-point
full on the pads and he clips it very well but short midwicket intercepts, well stopped I'd have to say, as the ball was timed well and with power
another back-foot defensive to a shortish one, another thick inside-edge, this one onto the thigh, and again some smart calling get them a single
back of a length and he gets in line to defend back to Broad's right
full and he drives hard, too much bottomhand, and gets an inside-edge towards Pietersen at midwicket
gets back and defends a shortish one to Collingwood at point
there's a good length and thats driven towards extra cover
on the stumps and he gets back in his crease to defend
starts off short on the body and Taylor has to drop it down at his feet
shorter still, Taylor pulls but the ball bobs up off his gloves into the massive space backward of square leg and he survives
stays on the back foot and pulls another short one to midwicket
there's a good length, getting How back in his crease, defending
short on middle and off and wristily worked to midwicket

good shout, as that one pitches on leg stump and raps How's pad, as he shuffles and is late on the shot, but Steve Davis shakes his head, looks to be a bit high perhaps .. replays suggest it would have taken the top of the bails
on the stumps and thats worked towards the man at midwicket
full and he comes forward, driving on the up but to right to cover
extra pace and bounce on that one, landing in a sweet channel, getting Taylor forward and pushing with no footwork, and he's beaten
thats more a drivable length and he does so, but finds cover again
well stopped at point by Collingwood, after Taylor eases forward and square-drives the full one hard, and good covering up as the ball rolled to his left
good length, good channel, good lift, Taylor leaves it be for Ambrose
lands on middle and leg and carries on high, he gets an inside-edge to point, scampering a run as his partner calls him on
too straight that time but Taylor cannot beat midwicket on the shot
slides outside his leg stump as he shuffles across to try and tickle it fine, there's calls of 'catch it' but thats also a wide
much fuller on off stump and pleasantly pushed with a very straight bat back past the bowler and stumps for a well-run single
short again, sliding down the pads and Davis spreads his arms again
short of a length and How hops up to defend, rather stoically

dangerous, dangerous ... How gets right in front of his stumps and has to hurriedly bring his bat down in time, as he was shaping to work it away but the ball straighted on him ... had he missed, he was a goner
straighter delivery and this time he does get back to defend, better
too straight and he drives that down to the man at mid-on
comes forward and drives on the up but to an alert Bell at short cover
back of a length and its defended to Collingwood at point
too full and thats crunched hard, but straight to mid-off
get back and defends one to cover again
another maiden, second on the trot, Taylor defending a slower ball
oh, good delivery, right through him outside off, he was lucky not to edge that one
defended hard on the front foot
on the front foot now and pushed to midwicket, they run through the single
pinched the single again, this time with a push to the covers and a handy scamper through
a stubborn, prodding kind of defence now, worked forward to mid on
strayed on to the legs, and driven forward without much power towards mid on
poor shot, frustration as the pressure had been building - he thinks he's received a pullable ball but succeeds only in crashing a thick edge right back into middle stump
dug out off the front foot and the legs towards mid on
great shot, takes one step down the track and drives flowingly through the covers, finding the gap
pushed out on the back foot to point
a lifter this time, he just lets it go through
bowling! Pace and bounce and Styris is in some trouble, curving his back right out of the way as a searching bouncer rockets over and way above middle stump
some swing away, fired in and yet the ball dies a touch - just a smidgen - as it's chased away from the body
on the front foot, wristed on the front foot out to midwicket
gone now, some lift off the deck and Styris shapes to evade but can't get his hands down in time and the ball comes off the gloves and is snapped appreciatively by Ambrose
stays over the wicket, forced across him, again a touch of lift and the batsman lets it go through
across him again, but a touch straighter and it goes through to the keeper
oh, bowled. Forced across him once more and the batsman has a poke at it off the back foot
full delivery, digs out the yorker in line with off. He's certainly a thinker is Broad
drags it down a touch short, Taylor plays off the back foot, well fielded by Swann in the covers and it's picked up and thrown back towards the stumps, but with a wide throw, Bopara backing up
some width outside off, flays hard off the back foot but scythes only air
defended hard on the front foot
good delivery here from Broad removes the dangerous Taylor, sneaking through the defences as Taylor looked to play it from outside off, and the full ball nips back and knocks back off stump
a dot ball ends the over and Broad has some well-deserved figures
forced past him, with some swing, the ball nips back a little bit and goes through to Ambrose
forced across him, the batsman shoulders arms
hurried through down the channel, this time the batsman shoulders arms
bangs it in across him once more, forced off the back foot to the covers. Alert, the batsmen look for the single but realise it would be too risky
width across him, the batsman shoulders arms
looks to turn it from outside off with a whip into the leg side, but doesn't quite get the timing
forced hard across him again
on the legs, squeezed out in front of square
short on middle and leg, looks to push it with the wrists to midwicket, but doesn't quite get the purchase he was looking for
on off stump this time, defended on the front foot
outside off, worked down off the back foot to third man
short ball, thinks about going for it, but lets it through at the last second
comes in hard and straight and clamps down just in time, getting some bat on it, on the front foot
forced across him outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
outside off, the batsman pushes at it away from his body as the ball leaves him off the deck
forced off the back foot into the covers
dragged a touch short outside off, it's cut hard, well and quickly but Collingwood is waiting there at point to cut it off much to Flynn's chagrin
the ball goes through outside off on a good length this time
some width outside off, the batsman cuts hard at it
defended hard on the front foot into the covers
goes through on a good length outside off, the batsman lets it go through
nips back in from outside off, the batsman plays down in defence, looking to tuck it off the hips but not quite getting the timing
played down off the back foot once more
short ball outside off
this one goes right past the outside edge
outside off, and the batsman works it out to square - ironic cheers for a rare run
worked into the covers this time
on the legs, squeezed out square and he commands his partner to "Wait!"
short ball, defended down
outside off, cut down into the track in front of point
outside off, drives hard at one which offers just that extra, tempting bit of width
some shape away, the batsman lets it go through
defended back down into the track from a line in line with off
short ball, the batsman ducks right under it as it follows right across him
outside off, defends off the back foot into the covers
short ball outside off, worked off the back foot down to third man where it's side-armed back to the keeper
in line with off, defended into the covers
short and a touch wide bit, he stands his ground and cuts, missing
short of a length and Elliott gets back and defends it to cover
that one sits up and rises and again Elliott  plays and misses, not moving his feet and wafting off the back foot
gets bat on that one, pushing off the back foot to Collingwood at point
firmly stroked by Flynn this time, off the back foot, but straight to cover

good grief, he's got a wicket with a full toss! Out slips a gentle full loosener as Anderson slips at delivery point, but would you believe, Flynn's attempted pull simply balloons up and nestles in mid-on's palms
on the stumps and he nudges that past midwicket to raise the 50
tries to work this one down to fine leg but cant, runs the leg-bye instead
short of a length and he tries to work it across but mistimes the shot
sits up just outside off and he taps it to an alert Collingwood
pitches on leg and squares him up, ends up running it to Collingwood
lands on a length and goes on, and thats a quiet end to the over
back of a length and he plays that towards the man at cover
too much width and Elliott cuts that wide of backward point for one
pokes at one off the back foot, beaten by bounce and movement
changes the length and gets Elliott defending this one back
bouncer this time, sailing over his left shoulder, wide called for height
back of a length and sliding in and he defends it back to Anderson
there's a positive shot, leaning forward and driving out to deep cover
good channel, seaming away, and he leaves it be
shorter and he adjusts to tuck off the hips past square leg
sits up and he withdraws the bat as the ball angles in
gets onto the toes and pushes this one to the man at point
back of a length and pushed to Collingwood, this is stifling stuff
defends and runs this one just wide of slip for runs to third man
back of a length and pushed to point again, no chance there
stays a tad low but he gets back and defends to Wright in time
short but he gets away with it because Collingwood is a livewire at backward point, sliding across and cutting off a firm back-foot shot by Elliott
tucks him up but he gently nudges that to midwicket for one
change of pace, full on middle and off and pushed back to Wright
hits a good length and Elliott gets back to push to cover
starts off full and Hopkins drives, getting an inside-edge onto boot
back of a length and pushed straight to Bell at cover this time
identical stuff, Hopkins unable to beat Bell, who moves in closer
short one, sits up and he shapes to pull but ends up dropping it down
now he pushes a fuller one to Bell again, to get back to business
thats overpitched and driven out past cover for a single, yoo hoo
thats streaky, as he reaches out and half-steers-have-edges in the air through the gap wide of gully out to Porterfield at third man
gets forward and drives this one to mid-off, who runs in
holds back the length and Elliott gets back to defend to Wright
defends off the front foot and edges down towards backward point
stands and wafts at one but cannot make contact

dropped, but that would have made for a stunner! Hopkins squirts a wide one in the air to backward point, where Collingwood leaps horizontally to his right, gets hands on it, but fails to hold on ... that was hit hard and still counts as a catch, harsh as it sounds ... that said, its Collingwood, who has pulled off blinders
fullish length and he plays it to cover that time
too much width and he cuts it late and past backward point for two
more room but he dabs this one to the fielder now
pitches around leg stump and slides down, raps the pads as he tries to nudge towards midwicket, they all clear their throats but umpire Hartley shakes his head
comes forward and works this one into the gap for one
well bowled, nipping it in off a length and Hopkins is nearly cut in half as he plays, ball clips thigh pad before Ambrose takes and Hartley doesn't respond to the appeal for caught-behind
well now, whats this? A boundary, first since the 12th over no less, as Elliott slaps the rank short ball very well into the space between cover and point, nice shot
inches forward and defends that one rather positively
on the and clips it down to fine leg, where Tremlett dives
gets forward and leaves that one be outside off stump
gets forward and taps to cover, urgently sprinting out of the blocks
too straight but he just taps that to midwicket
more room and he eases back to steer backward of point for one
short on the stumps, Hopkings gets inside the line and plays a feeble pull of sorts but the ball goes nowhere

and there he goes, actually timing the pull shot much better than the last attempt, but not good enough to beat deep fine leg, where the substitute Porterfield steadies himself, runs back and holds an easy catch
good length on middle and off and watchfully defended back
gets forward and pushes this one back
bouncer to end the over and he sways out the ball's way
stands his ground, pokes a short one past point for two out to sweeper
fuller length, pushed across Vettori, who leaves it be with a twirl
full on off stump and defended with a straight bat to Wright
better length and it gets Vettori defending to cover
offered some width, he goes for an expansive cut but cant connect
pushed across wider this time and he shoulders arms
comes onto the front foot and drives a full one to Pietersen at cover
worked wide of the crease, Vettori has a look and decides to leave
gets forward and defends this one to point
fuller, sits up a touch and he lets it through to Ambrose
thats too straight and pleasantly on-driven down the ground for four
gets up and runs a wider one to Bopara at point
on the pads and tucked to midwicket, who shies and misses his mark
well outside leg, Vettori can't get bat on it and wide is the call
comes forward and drives to KP at extra cover, who allows the ball through his legs and he's not too happy with himself, neither is Wright
has a flirt with a short and wide one but fails to get bat on it
outside leg again and worked off the pads to short fine leg, Ambrose fields
still he slides it down the pads, to the right-hander now, and its escorted down to the fielder at fine leg for another easy single
full and wide, Vettori under-edges the cut shot and thats drinks
opens the face and runs this one down to third man, where Anderson returns a low direct hit but it ricochets, Ambrose gets there before the batsmen try and run
back of a length and this one is defended off the back foot
gets forward and plays this one to cover
full and loopy outside off, he waits and dabs it wide of point
short of a length and he defends towards backward point
uses the width and lack of pace to run this down to third man
tossed up outside off stump and driven straight to cover
much flatter, driven back down the track and Swann stops it
touch flatter, Elliott waits for spin and stabs it to backward point
full on middle and off and driven back to Swann's left side
now he strides well forward and drives on the up past mid-off
flat outside leg stump and he drives that to midwicket
short and straight and Michael Atherton reckons it could have been a wide and is aghast when it's not given
more of the short stuff, forces the batsman to curve back his chest
steps outside off to gladly accept the easy offering, and that's a fine cover drive, on the front foot and drive nhard
tucks him up this time, pushes down in defence in line with off
outside off, pushed into the covers and they ease through
clipped off the legs through the 45 to bring up the hundred and New Zealand fans in the crowd are delighted by this
on the front foot, wrists it out towards Bopara who slides in, doesn't quite stop the ball, but it plugs in the turf
straight drive out to long off and Shah is very lazy in the chase and his throw back is quite weak - Swann is furious they have come back for two
steps forward and drives in front of midwicket
outside off, the batsman comes out and drives off the legs
outside off, pushes off the legs to short midwicket
outside off again, pushed off the bat to the gully this time
oh, dropped perhaps, Ambrose diving to his left and it smashed through the webbing
defended forward
oh, an inside edge skews off ... but square and safe
outside off, cut hard to point
short on middle and leg and Vettori is quick to pull it round to square leg
some swing outside off, the batsman strides out and drives to the covers
turned in from outside off and pulled round behind square

on to the front foot, pushed out to the covers and Vettori has to slide at full stretch to get back in the crease - Collingwood's throw would have been out if he had hit, and Vettori somehow draws himself up very, very quickly ready to look for the second
pushed out forward
pushed out forward once more

soft dismissal, Vettori waits for it to turn away from him and then drives up to mid on where Shah comes round and watches the ball right into his hands, Vettori having reached away from his body and stopped on the shot, neither of which were good ideas
some big turn back in from outside off, worked to the legs, a direct hit could have been close
defended on the front foot
swept round to fine leg
defended forward
short and pushed down off the back foot and the hips
driven out to mid off where Tremlett is quick in the return
stout and solid in defence
drives out wide of mid on
some turn back in from outside off and he defends it down without too much fuss
hits the spot, and forces the defence once more
pushed off the legs behind square
turned back in a touch from outside off and pushed back out to the covers
turned in from outside off again, worked out to midwicket but there's no way through for New Zealand
tucked off the hips from in line with off and out to the legs
some swing away outside off, the batsman strides out and presses towards mid off
defended on the front foot
outside off, squeezed out to point
short outside off and hook-swivelled round to square
on the front foot and pushed out to the covers
turned back in from outside off, defended on the front foot
outside off, and a genuine edge from the top of Mills' blade as he pushes out to drive
pushed forward to the covers, more defensively than anything, and they elect not to take the single
comes in on the front foot, squeezed out to the covers and will they run? "No!"
outside off, comes back in a touch and a big controlled edge runs down to Broad at deep third man
comes in on off, defended forward
on middle, pushed out to midwicket
steps back to give himself room to launch into a hard drive but finds the man at extra cover
bouncer, Mills sways away from it
on the legs, pushed out in front of square and they charge through quickly
some seam away, the batsman works it out to point
pushed down into the legs and they run through, Collingwood has completed his ten overs
nips in from outside off and worked out to gully
comes in on the legs, pushed forward defensively
defended on the front foot in line with off
outside off, sways back, the ball goes on through to the keeper
pushed out on the front foot
defended on the front foot
tucked down off the hips
played off the legs
on the front foot, pushed out
an appeal as he's rapped on the leg, but the ball was going down leg and it's quickly turned down
squeezed out to square
brushed off the legs to fine leg
driven hard to the covers
somehow that missed everything, the batsman backing way back to give himself room, the ball bouncing over middle stump
played on the front foot
full toss, pushed out to the covers. One of those days where fielders seem to be everywhere
moves way back and cuts out hard and they steal a second single from a direct hit from Collingwood that cannons off
big booming wide down the leg side and it's called appropriately.
lets it go through this time
pushed out to mid on
outside off, the ball moves away and the batsman chases after it, fruitlessly
outside off, opens the face and runs it down to third man to bring up his fifty from 99 balls and it's well cheered
backs right away, the short one following him towards the leg, and the more he curves away the more the ball seems to follow him. He gets right away from it - at last
short ball outside off, and Mills has already backed away before cutting up and over point
responds with a would-be yorker, which is dug out towards the covers
goes big! Mills climbs into a fullish delivery from Anderson, flatbatting a drive right over mid off and he gets the maximum after a full swing
pushed into the covers
goes for the yorker, but it's a poor full toss which Elliott cuts through backward point and the partnership continues
...and he'll have to have another walk - this one a wide outside off
just a touch short this time but it's pulled easily out to deep square leg

but Anderson strikes at last, banging in a short ball which Elliott goes to hook, Wright sets himself at deep midwicket and then realises he's slightly misjudged it, steps back and clings on as the ball carries him to the ground with the momentum
...but he will take the four instead, Mills looking to defend a short, dipping straight one, but the inside edge cuts a merry path to the keeper's left and on through a very fine, fine leg
slower ball and Southee steps back and carves up high and higher and over towards long on where Pietersen waits and takes a low catch by his knees, tumbling forward at the same time
some width outside off and there's a crashing drive through the covers by Mills, coming right out of his crease to meet a short one
down on one knee and drives straight and true and that one carries right over the rope, much to the delight of the crowd
backs away, short ball, curves his back away

dipping full toss on off and that's a squandered opportunity for Tremlett, who comes right inside the line of it  at long off and the ball bounces over his shoulder as he slides, and carries on to the rope
Mills goes on the final ball, going for the hard pull and a top edge deviates up and out to Collingwood at point who takes the catch

inn2.comm: and he's off the mark with a tuck to midwicket as Mills struggles for line
shuffles across his stumps and works one wide of square leg for two
fuller and wider, in search of outswing, and Wright leaves it be
edged and taken, Wright feeling for one pitched up outside off stump and swinging away, and the catch is taken low to his right by Styris at second slip
welcome, says Mills, bouncing him with a snorter that rears up and hustles past Pietersen's face as he does well to drop the hands out of the ball's way
short of a length and he gets tall on the toes to defend it back
gentle swing and Bell fishes for it outside off, beaten by movement and the lack of footwork ... an interesting chase lined up, I reckon
beaten again as he gets onto the toes and feels for it outside off stump
gets well out of his crease, shuffling, and tucks the ball from off stump into the space behind square leg for an easy single
gets some room, stays back in his crease, and chops the ball to cover
again, well deep, stands tall and drives off the back foot to Flynn at cover
there's a half-tracker, way outside the stumps and over Hopkins for wides, spoiling what was a tidy over so far
skips down and tries to work the ball towards leg, bat turning in his hands, but Gillespie drops it short and the ball squeezes past bat to the 'keeper
short of a length and gaining on Bell, who leaves and Hopkins takes
tidy line, short of a length once more and Bell just leaves it be
a touch wider but still a tidy length and Bell lets it pass again
gets bat on this one, defending it down to backward point
on middle and off and Bell defends it towards midwicket
too much movement, pitching outside leg and beating Hopkins
back of a length and he gets forward to defend it
invites the uppish drive outside off stump but he shoulders arms
closer to the stumps and Pietersen turns it to midwicket
that one holds its line and straightens, beating his forward prod
straightens again and Pietersen is almost squared up as he shapes to whip it away to midwicket again, plays it back to Gillespie
back of a length, hint of swing, and he leaves it alone
shortish length but this time he hops across to work it to midwicket

nearly, nearly ... Mills bangs it in short and gets it to move and bounce onto Bell, who fends at it poorly and looks on with his heart in his mouth as the ball takes the splice and pops up to land shortly wide of backward point
fuller now and he defends with an outside-edge to gully
too short and wide and thats thumped with power through the covers
got 'em! Pietersen goes, flicking the full ball across the line straight to Elliott at midwicket, who cups it in front of his face
good length, swinging away outside off stump, Bopara leaves
fuller and bouncing a touch, after swinging in, and Bopara withdraws the top hand to avoid hurting his nuckles
punches the short one off the back foot to cover, where Flynn fumbles
slides down the pads, Bopara tickles and Hopkins saves on the bounce
comes into him off a short length and he gets behind to defend
slower ball and Bopara clips that off the pads straight to midwicket
good length, asking him to drive, but he resists and lets it pass
tucks him up for room and Bopara can only defend it to Flynn at cover
short on the stumps, Bell moves across to work it in the air to midwicket and sets off, Elliott swoops in and throws at the stumps but just misses
too straight but he's late on the shot, turning it to square leg
lifts a touch off a good length and Bopara holds back on the cut
pushes it up closer and fuller and now he leaves off the front foot
very tidy bowling, a good off-stump line and he can only defend
fuller this time, swinging in, and Bopara defends with a straight bat
right in the corridor of uncertainty and Bell gets across to leave it be
presses him back in his crease, Bell dropping the head and defending
inches forward, then senses the ball swinging in from wide and leaves
zips back in sharply and catches him in the midriff area, bat very late
fuller and wider, but again Bell is just comfortable letting it go
short and wide and cut hard but he can't beat Flynn at cover
on the pads but he's late on the attempted flick towards square

short and wide, rising too, and Bopara gives it the kitchen sink, slashing up and over backward point, then Southee comes sprinting across from third man and leaps forward to try and get a hand to it but he has no chance
back of a length and he plays this one with a straight bat
pitches on leg and gains on Bopara, rapping him high on the flap
too straight and well placed into the gap at square leg for two
ripper to end the over, seaming, lifting and beating his back-foot push
good start, back of a length on off stump and defended by Bell
back of a length again and defended off the back foot this time
full now and he drives to mid-off, where Vettori throws but misses, Bopara wanted one but Bell sent him back firmly
change of pace, on a length and Bell turns that to midwicket
well stopped! Bell cuts the short one well down to backward point, where How dives to his left and saves runs
goes for an expansive cover-drive with no footwork and misses
defended hard on the front foot in line with off
inside edged over leg stump, Mills firing in one which cut back in off the seam and the ball travels quickly towards the rope
outside off, shoulders arms and lets the ball go through
outside off, shoulders arms as the ball goes through on a good length
outside off, lets this one through, too
clipped well off the legs, just behind square and Umpire Hartley uses his radio to see if Southee's slide had connected with the ball and rope simultaneously
some swing outside off, plenty of width on that one
outside off ,shoulders arms as that one goes through
some width outside off and a hard cut off the back foot with some flair too, the ball rockets to the fence in front of point
follows up with a beauty, good length outside off and some swing after pitching, Bopara draws the bat right inside the line of the ball on the back foot
swished off the toes through square
pushed on to the legs and lifted off the shins through midwicket
defended on the front foot in line with off
pushed into the covers off the back foot
outside off, cut into the ground off the back foot and Bopara rehearses improving the shot
on middle and off, wristed into the leg side albeit sans much power of which to speak. In another words, a dot
comes on the front foot and defends hard in line with off
defended back down the line of off
on the legs, driven out to short midwicket
outside off, cut down to third man
on the off stump, turned away to deep midwicket
on middle and leg, pushed away to midwicket
defended down to the gully on the front foot
outside off, played down to the gully
kicks off from this end with a wide, a swinging one way outside off
neat from Bell who tucks well off his hips in front of square. A cool pull
down the track and watches it swing away down the channel
poor ball outside off, short and wide and Bell is hardly going to miss out, cutting hard out of the middle with some power, ending up on his back foot
this is a silken cover drive this time, Bell taking full advantage this over. That one also out of the middle
on the back foot, defended right back down
defended right back down in line with middle and off
lets this one go through
takes the pace off it, so slow Bopara has time to think about it and works it from off to square
some swing away, good length and just outside off, fools Bell into playing at it away from the body
some swing away, left alone
defended right back down into the covers
wide ball outside off, a soft dismissal there and he walks off shaking his head after playing far away from his body and cutting to McCullum who makes no mistake in the covers
some swing away, played off the back foot down
again played down off the back foot
more defence in line with off
played off the legs behind square, a shout of "Bowler, bowler" and indeed it comes in at the end. A direct hit and he was in some trouble
blinding catch! Bopara goes as the short ball comes in, and he cuts off the back foot hard as you like, How dives to his left and snaps up a superb catch
defended hard first up in line with off
driven on the front foot to the covers
some swing away down the channel, pushed into the covers
on the front foot, pushed to midwicket
outside off, lets it go through
driven to the covers
felt for the ball outside off
good bouncer, bobs under it
edged and gone! Shah goes for a duck, driving away from his body and it's snapped at second slip
lets this one go through outside off
outside off, played into the covers
outside off, good length, chases at it away from the body
big edge, the ball moving off the seam and then carrying to first slip where Taylor juggles, parries it up as he snaps at it but takes it on the second grasp
outside off, pushed into the covers off the back foot
outside off, some wild swing away, the batsman shoulders arms
much of the same there, plenty of swing around at least...
down the legs and helped easily on its way to the rope
on to the legs again, a smidgen straighter, but flicked well down to long leg
some width outside off, cut into the covers
bobs down under the bouncer
overpitched on the legs, flicked out to square and they accept the single
on the legs, pushed to the leg side
bouncer tracks past him as he curves his back out of the way
more excellent bowling, some swing away after hitting the deck just outside off, Collingwood's tempted into prodding at it
outside off and drilled into the covers off the back foot
outside off, lets it go down the channel this time
some width outside off and Collingwood cuts hard in front of point off the back foot
outside off, straightens on and the batsman nearly edges through to a fumbling keeper
outside off, played into the covers
outside off, played down off the back foot into the covers now
defended on the front foot
a huge appeal as the ball comes in on the pads, but it looked to have struck him just outside off
defended hard into it. Great start from Vettori, the sort of thing we're accustomed to from him
backs way away, Collingwood gets distracted and sort of half plays a shot at it, the ball just going on over the stumps. All very bizarre
drives back to the bowler, the ball coming off some point of him and carrying on towards the non-striker's stumps
drives into the covers on the front foot
ducked right down and let the ball carry on past the shoulder
some swing away, a short ball outside off and a thick outside edge carries down without too much trouble to third man
outside off, played out off the back foot in front of point
brushed off the legs to fine leg
floated up there in line with off, defended on the front foot
on the front foot once more, defended back down the track
dragged it down a touch, cut off the back foot down behind point
on the front foot, an edge out towards short midwicket
down the track and he was beaten in the flight initially but carried on through with the stroke all the same, despatching it hard and flat over long on. Good strike
defended down
defended forward
dragged it down a touch short and Collingwood gets hold of a firm pull swivelled in front of midwicket from outside off
an unconvincing inside edge skews out to midwicket
short ball, outside off, cut out to point
right up there on off, forcing him into the back-foot defensive
on off, once again defended back down
flat on the stumps, worked towards midwicket and he sprints off
slower through the air, off stump, and Collingwood defends
sees him skipping down and fires it onto his boots
a bit of air again, and Collingwood gets well forward to defend
teases him with a fuller delivery and Collingwood pats it back
too short, Collingwood waits to see if it turns and then cuts it fine
gentle loosener outside off stump, moves away, left alone
up there again, asking him to chase, but Collingwood doesn't react
now he gives it a biff, cracking off the back foot into the gap at cover
chases a full and wide one, feet not moving as he wafts and misses
close! This one jags back in and Swann is late on getting the bat down, the inside-edge drops perilously close to off stump and then bounces over the top
good shot, forcing the shorter one off the back foot past Flynn at cover
flat on middle and leg, worked away with the turn past midwicket
some good dip there, middle and off, and its defended
comes forward, Vettori fires it in, and Collingwood defends
skips down again, once more its flat, and he pats it to midwicket
full on middle and leg and turned to midwicket
goes for a sweep and connects decently enough, placing it fine
full and honing into leg stump, Swann misses the flick, Gillespie and Hopkins belt out and appeal but umpire Hartley reckons it would have missed ... hmmm
drives off the front foot with an inside-edge towards point
gets pinned in his crease and defends with one hand off the bat
too short and thats pulled along the ground past square leg
chops a shorter one into the ground in front of backward point
tidy, very tidy .. short of a length and he defends it back to Gillespie
slow yet flat and he misses out on the defensive, but gets struck well outside the line of off stump on that occasion
short and wide and he's now late on the cut, missing completely
oversteps, Swann cuts that towards point, so we have a free hit
charges down and biffs this one well and hard over mid-off, top shot
poor fielding from Mills out at deep square leg, allowing the ball through his legs after Swann pulls off a well-connected sweep shot
flat on middle and leg and he pushes that one back
sweeps one off line but Vettori's stuck in a short fine leg now
full and swinging in but wide enough for Collingwood to leave
good length this time and he defends that off the front foot to point
full on middle and leg and inside-eged, on the drive, to midwicket
hits a good length, gets it to sit up, and Collingwood leaves
nips in off a shorter length but he works it behind square for a single
full and sliding down leg stump, Swann survives with a thick inside-edge back onto the legs after trying to whip that away over square leg ... how many legs in that sentence, then?
short of a length and Collingwood defends with an angled bat, suggesting he wanted to get across and turn it towards midwicket
pulls that from outside off stump but there's cover in the deep, Taylor
on leg stump and Swann can only tap it to midwicket
short of a length but wide enough for Swann to dab past point for one
gets back and pokes this one towards cover, where How runs across from point and collects and then throws down the track but its off the mark and a diving Collingwood is safe
slow bouncer now, surprising Swann, who ducks under it
right there on off stump and Collingwood pats it back to Gillespie
drivable length and he eases that off the front to Flynn at cover
back of a length, holds its line, and he watches it through to Hopkins
comes down and ends up defending a length ball back the way
oye, this one hits the seam and goes away from Collingwood, who is sucked forward and pushes at it, beaten by the movement
gets forward and defends with a straight bat to cover to end the over
sits up short and Swann is nearly tempted into a poke, but holds back just at the right moment as the ball rears up
pokes this one off the back foot, but straight to backward point
short on off stump, he backs away and pushes to point again
firmly slashed off the front foot, up and over cover, but just for one
too short and he latches onto a firm pull but deep midwicket is in place
top edge as Swann gets onto the toes and pushes the short one over backward point, nearly carrying to a sliding Southee, running in from third man
back of a length well wide and thats left alone by Swann
comes back in but he gets forward and runs it to backward point
gets tall and runs a shortish one past gully for one out to Gillespie
a bit too straight and Collingwood can tuck that out to midwicket
well played, just blasting the short and wide delivery off the back foot up and over the covers and the sweeper cannot get there in time
now he pushes himself onto the front foot and opens the face, playing it ito the gap in front of point and runs hard, aided by Collingwood, despite the dodgy hamstring
gets forward, then back, and dabs the ball towards point

pitches outside off stump, gets the cutter to nip back in and catch Collingwood in his crease, appeals, but umpire Davis shakes his head as the ball was indeed carrying on over the top of the bails .. Swann calls for the leg-bye
eases forward and drives this one to point
slips out and goes well down leg stump for a wide
another shot full of intent, bat and pad married as he drives past cover
on leg stump, he shuffles and nudges down to deep square leg
soft dismissal! Styris bowls it on middle and leg and Swann's battling innings ends with a lazy chip to a waiting Taylor at midwicket, much like the way Pietersen went earlier
thats a good length and he defends it patiently to point
gets across and flicks this one across the line to midwicket, sprinting
slower ball, very full and angled across and he leaves it alone
hits a length and stays low but he gets bat down on time

offered some room, he gets tall and punches this ever so sweetly off the back foot and into the gap at cover, but some excellent chasing, sliding, and returning from McCullum, hauling it back just inside the boundary, impresses no less
fuller and wider, with good lift of the track, and he leaves it alone
a bouncer, pretty high over the stumps and Steve Davis calls wide
short, Broad hops across and pushes to short catching cover
short again but this time he gets tall and whips that from off stump wide of midwicket, another good shot getting him three more
short and wide and gets on top of it, cutting past point for two more
too straight and Collingwood clips it out to deep backward square
short of a length and Broad plays another back-foot punch to cover
pushes this across the stumps and Broad shoulders arms
good length, not offering Collingwood any room, and he defends
short of a length and he defends off the back foot
good line there, bringing Collingwood forward to defend, elbow high et al
thats the spot, and Collingwood again defends towards point
thats the wrong line, allowing him a clipped single to deep square leg
short of a length and Broad pushes off the back foot past point for one
tossed up from over the stumps, Broad reaches forward and defends, getting an edge wide of slip for a single
fuller and quicker, driftfing in on leg stump, Collingwood is late on the shot and gets rapped in front of about leg but umpire Davis shakes his head, that was a close shout
slower through the air and he defends that to cover
fired in flat and he clips that to the man at midwicket for one
gets across his stumps and works it to midwicket
gets a single this time, tucking the ball wide of midwicket
overpitched outside off but Broad square-drives to How at point
chases one with zero footwork and is beaten as the ball straightens
slower one swings through the air, almost a low yorker, and strikes Broad on low on the pad outside the line of impact, there's a noise too, suggesting a thin inside-edge
short now and he gets back to punch it to the man at cover
full on off stump and he plays a straight drive, which Southee fields
drives one thats wider and runs it off the edge past gully for one
full and flat outside off and he flicks it down to mid-on for one
uses his feet and clips a full and flat one down past square leg
tossed up slower, beating Broad's drive, Hopkins whips off the bails but that back leg was well inside the line
slow again, dipping low, Broad gets struck well outside the line
intelligently bowled, landing this one on middle and off and he defends
flat delivery to end the over and Broad flicks to mid-on for a single
angles the ball across Broad, who gets in and leaves it be
top shot, getting over a short one and cutting past point for one
shuffles across and flicks the full ball out to deep backward square
drives a wide one and edges just wide of Taylor at gully

gone, Southee! Thats his fourth wicket of the day, and what a big one, pitching just outside off stump, swinging it in and rapping Collingwood below the knee roll as he hops and is late on the shot, umpire raises his finger
full on leg stump, worked via the leg-bye to square leg, ending a top spell from Southee, just 19
full and flat on middle and off and defended to leg
a bit short but Tremlett doesnt get bat on the attempted cut
wrong line, sliding down leg stump and he tucks it fine for a single
slider this time, catching Broad just outside off stump, late on the shot
flat again, and quicker, Broad misses again as the ball slides on, Vettori appeals but the umpire is unmoved, replays show it clipping the bails, Vettori is livid
reaches out and drives to cover, a misfield in the deep gets him a couple
full and straight and Tremlett taps it back to Elliott
gets back and pushes a shorter one straight to point
ooh beaten there, wafting at one of the back foot
beaten again by the fuller one that comes in and misses his drive
slower ball, top stuff on a length and thats pushed to point
short but down leg stump and he tucks it in the air wide of square leg
too full on leg stump and Tremlett flicks a single to midwicket
too flat and he shuffles, tucking the ball to square leg for one
full and flat outside off stump, defended with an edge to short third man
full and flat again, down leg, and clipped to midwicket

what a catch down the leg side! Brilliant! Vettori serves it up down the leg side, giving it a bit of a tweak, Broad shapes to work it around the corner but gets the faintest of tickles on it and Hopkins, shuffling to his right, holds the deflection very well
pushed wide of off stump and Anderson has a bit of a flirt at it
nips in to hit his back leg, but well down leg stump, and high

all over and New Zealand have levelled the series! Tremlett plays a true tailender's slog, top-edging it up in the air for Vettori to hold a dolly at cover, and he releases the ball with plenty of emotion as his team-mates converge
